<paragraph blockId="16.[136,323,590,617]" box="[136,323,590,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,323,590,617]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,323,590,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">
3. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[164,254,590,617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Hirtella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,254,590,617]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="192" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,662,797]" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">
Phylogenetic analyses (
<figureCitation box="[403,469,662,688]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[280,1309,540,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-166@3.[268,1320,530,1808]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Combined Bayesian half-compatible phylogenetic tree of Couepia and its sister lineages. Bayesian posterior probabilities are shown above branches. The outgroup taxon, Euphronia guianensis, is not displayed due to its long branch lengths." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142508/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spruce ex Prance" authorityYear="1972" box="[557,677,663,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Couepia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[557,677,663,689]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">C. recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a clade with other members of American 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1192,1281,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Hirtella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1281,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These results, together with fruit morphological characters, strongly support the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spruce ex Prance" authorityYear="1972" box="[1001,1118,699,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Couepia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[1001,1118,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">C. recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1261,1350,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Hirtella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1261,1350,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sothers &amp; Prance" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Spruce ex Prance" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Hirtella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Hirtella recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Prance" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[362,457,735,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Couepia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,457,735,761]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Couepia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the greater number of stamens and the usually narrow, elongate receptacle, although this character occurs in a few 
<taxonomicName box="[423,603,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Hirtella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[423,512,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">Hirtella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuatrecasas (1950: 59)" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityPageNumber="59" authorityYear="1950" box="[661,1062,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chrysobalanaceae" genus="Hirtella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiflora">
<emphasis box="[661,793,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="192">H. tubiflora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cuatrecasas, J." box="[800,1062,770,797]" pageId="16" pageNumber="192" pagination="55 - 113" refId="ref13072" refString="Cuatrecasas, J. (1950) Studies of South American plants II. Fieldiana, Botany 27: 55 - 113." type="journal article" year="1950">Cuatrecasas (1950: 59)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
